## STEP 5 — Module Explanations

### `/platform` — Shared SDK

| Module | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `sdk/auth/` | Single source of token refresh, session persistence, OAuth flows — shared by web, desktop, mobile |
| `sdk/api/` | Versioned HTTP client with interceptors; all platforms use the same endpoint constants |
| `sdk/socket/` | Socket.IO factory + canonical event map so desktop/mobile never hardcode event strings |
| `sdk/crypto/` | Portable E2EE using Web Crypto API (browser/Node) and `react-native-quick-crypto` (mobile) via same interface |
| `sdk/notifications/` | Abstract notification bridge: web push → desktop OS notifications → FCM/APNs on mobile |
| `sdk/upload/` | GCS presigned URL upload shared across all three clients |
| `sdk/sync/` | Offline queue + conflict resolution for multi-device sync |
| `types/` | TypeScript interfaces shared across all platforms (contract-first) |
| `constants/` | Socket event names, API versions — single source of truth |

### `/desktop` — Electron App

| Module | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `electron/main.js` | Main process: window creation, tray, auto-updater, deep links |
| `electron/preload.js` | Context bridge: exposes a safe `window.chttrix` API to renderer |
| `electron/ipc/handlers/` | OS capabilities: file system, Keychain, clipboard, shell |
| `renderer/bridge/` | Adapts `platform/sdk/*` for Electron environment (e.g. Keychain for crypto keys) |
| `renderer/overrides/` | CSS/JSX tweaks for native OS chrome (title bar, traffic lights) |
| `integrations/` | Google Calendar sync, macOS Spotlight, Windows Jump Lists |
| `build/` | electron-builder config for macOS (.dmg), Windows (.exe), Linux (.AppImage) |

### `/mobile` — React Native App

| Module | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `src/navigation/` | Stack + tab navigation using React Navigation v6 |
| `src/screens/` | Screen-level components mirroring web pages |
| `src/components/ui/` | Mobile-adapted design system (no DOM, RN primitives) |
| `src/bridge/` | Platform-specific adapters wrapping `platform/sdk/*` |
| `src/hooks/` | `useChttrixAuth`, `useChttrixSocket` — same logic, mobile-safe |
| `src/store/` | Redux Toolkit for predictable mobile state |
| `src/services/pushService.ts` | FCM token registration + APNs setup |
| `src/services/biometricService.ts` | Face ID / Touch ID / Fingerprint unlock |

### `/ai` — AI Intelligence Layer

| Module | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `orchestrator/` | Routes user queries to the correct agent, assembles workspace context |
| `agents/` | Specialized agents: Assistant, Summarizer, Automator, Insight, Workflow |
| `memory/` | Vector store adapters (Pinecone/Qdrant/pgvector) + hybrid retrieval |
| `prompt-engine/` | Versioned prompt templates with A/B testing support |
| `automation/` | Trigger → Condition → Action engine for workflow automation |
| `analytics-intelligence/` | Natural language insights, anomaly detection, auto-reports |
| `services/LLMProvider.js` | Abstraction over Gemini/OpenAI/Anthropic — swap models without code changes |
| `services/AIRateLimiter.js` | Per-workspace token budget to control cost |
| `api/` | Express routes mounted in server — `/api/v2/ai/*` |

