## STEP 9 — Recommended Development Order

### Phase 1 — Foundation (Weeks 1–3)
1. **Create `/platform/sdk`** — auth, api, socket, constants
2. **Refactor web client** to consume `platform/sdk/auth` and `platform/sdk/socket` (no breaking changes, drop-in)
3. **Establish `platform/types`** — TypeScript interfaces for all domain models

### Phase 2 — AI Layer (Weeks 4–8)
4. **Build `/ai/services/LLMProvider.js`** and extend existing `server/src/features/ai/`
5. **Set up `/ai/orchestrator/`** + `AssistantAgent` + `SummarizerAgent`
6. **Build `/ai/memory/`** — VectorStore with pgvector (low infra overhead)
7. **Wire `/ai/api/`** as `/api/v2/ai/*` in server
8. **Build `/ai/prompt-engine/`** with versioned templates
9. **Add `/ai/automation/`** engine with MessageTrigger + TimeTrigger

### Phase 3 — Desktop (Weeks 9–13)
10. **Scaffold Electron app** with `electron-builder`
11. **Build IPC handlers** (fs, notifications, keychain)
12. **Build renderer bridges** wrapping `platform/sdk/*`
13. **Integrate web client build** into Electron renderer
14. **OS integrations** (tray, auto-updater, deep links)

### Phase 4 — Mobile (Weeks 14–20)
15. **React Native project scaffold** (Expo or bare RN)
16. **Build mobile bridges** for auth, socket, crypto, notifications
17. **Build screens** (auth, messaging, channels, tasks)
18. **Redux store** setup
19. **Push notifications** (FCM + APNs)
20. **Biometric auth + offline sync**

---

## Architecture Decision Record (ADR) Summary

| Decision | Choice | Rationale |
|----------|--------|-----------|
| Monorepo structure | npm workspaces | Zero config, supports existing structure |
| SDK distribution | Internal workspace path | No private registry needed initially |
| Mobile state | Redux Toolkit | Predictable, DevTools, proven at scale |
| Vector DB | pgvector (Phase 1) → Pinecone (Phase 2) | Start low-cost, migrate when needed |
| AI provider | Gemini default + abstract provider | Existing Gemini integration, easy swap |
| Desktop build | electron-builder | Best-in-class, handles code signing |
| Mobile crypto | react-native-quick-crypto | JSI-based, near-native performance |
| Offline storage | Platform-specific via abstract interface | Best UX per platform, unified API |
